{{ChessProject|importance=Mid|class=Start}}

== Proposal to expand upon the 3. c3 "enhanced" Alapin line ==

What should black play after 3. c3? The only line that even approaches equality (by winning percentage) is e6. In every other line it seems white has a much easier time of it, with win percentages approaching double that of black. I referred to this as an "enhanced" Alapin as white gets an extra developed Knight due to black's essentially wasted h6.

{{ChessProject|importance=Mid|class=Stub}}

lol! why is this called the "Polish" gambit?? because it's a dumb move? how insulting!

:Openings called the "Polish" advance the b-pawn two squares forward at some point. It is not meant to be insulting. [[Special:Contributions/220.255.1.50|220.255.1.50]] ([[User talk:220.255.1.50|discuss]]) 08:43, 16 July 2011 (UTC)

