Here are a list of Windows 7 Shortcuts to help you work faster:
* Win+Up: Maximize * Win+Down: Restore / Minimize * Win+Left: Snap to left * Win+Right: Snap to right * Win+Shift+Left: Jump to left monitor * Win+Shift+Right: Jump to right monitor * Win+Home: Minimize / Restore all other windows * Win+T : Focus the first taskbar entry * Win+Space: Peek at the desktop * Win+G: Bring gadgets to the top of the Z-order * Win+P: External display options (mirror, extend desktop, etc) * Win+X: Mobility Center * Win+Spacebar: Aero desktop peek * Win+(1, 2,...,0): Open the corresponding taskbar pinned program; if already open, switch to that program * Ctrl+Click: on a pinned icon, cycle through open windows of that program * Ctrl+Shift+Click: on a pinned icon, runs a new instance of the program as administrator * Shift+Click: on a pinned icon, runs a new instance/window of the program
