{{Navlist/Top}}

This section covers advanced topics in grammar.

== What's in this section? ==

The parts of this section are:
*'''Aligning arguments''':  Morphosyntactic alignment &mdash; including theta roles, nominative-accusative, absolutive-ergative, split-ergative, Austronesian, active-stative, trigger, dechticaetiative.
*'''Forming words''':  Different strategies &mdash; including isolation/agglutination/inflection/fusion, polysynthesis, incorporation, oligosynthesis.
*'''Constraints on natural languages''':  Things that all natural-language grammars seem to have in common.
*'''Destroying the noun/verb distinction''':  Different ways to bend or break one of the most prominent constraints on natural languages.<br/>&nbsp;

